# Create the dataframe for plotting
# (1) Extract relevant columns and (2) sort by the column of interest
q1_df = raw_df[["distance_type", "noise_type", COLUMN_OF_INTEREST_Q1]].sort_values(COLUMN_OF_INTEREST_Q1)

# We store the relevant keys and the relevant keys per distance / noise for normalization
relevant_keys = [COLUMN_OF_INTEREST_Q1]
relevant_distance_keys = []
relevant_noise_keys = []

# Transform nominal data to separate columns and compute the cumulative sum for distance type entries
for distance_entry in ["Near", "Medium", "Far"]:
    distance_entry_key = f"distance_{distance_entry.lower()}" # Define the new column key
    relevant_distance_keys.append(distance_entry_key) # Store the new column key in the correct list
    q1_df[distance_entry_key] = np.where(q1_df["distance_type"] == distance_entry, 1, 0) # Actual data transformation
    q1_df[distance_entry_key] = q1_df[[distance_entry_key]].cumsum() # Compute the cumulative sum and overwrite column

# Transform nominal data to separate columns and compute the cumulative sum for noise type entries
#for noise_entry in ["no_noise", "salt", "hlines", "vlines", "straight_grid", "angled_grid",]:
for noise_entry in ["no_noise", "hlines", "vlines", "straight_grid", "angled_grid", "salt"]:
    noise_entry_key = f"noise_{noise_entry.lower()}" # Define the new column key
    relevant_noise_keys.append(noise_entry_key) # Store the new column key in the correct list
    q1_df[noise_entry_key] = np.where(q1_df["noise_type"] == noise_entry, 1, 0) # Actual data transformation
    q1_df[noise_entry_key] = q1_df[[noise_entry_key]].cumsum() # Comute the cumulative sum and overwrite columns

# Extend the relevant keys, which holds ALL column names, with the new cumulative distance and noise type column keys
relevant_keys.extend(relevant_distance_keys)
relevant_keys.extend(relevant_noise_keys)

# Normalize the cumulative data w.r.t. their absolute amount
q1_df[relevant_distance_keys] /= n_per_distance
q1_df[relevant_noise_keys] /= n_per_noise

# Finally extract only all relevant keys from the data frame
q1_df = q1_df[relevant_keys]

PX_THRESHOLD = 10 # Pixel threshold for figure
FIG_SCL = 1 # Scale factor for figure

#sns.set_style("whitegrid")
#sns.set_palette("colorblind")

# Apply the threshold

# Extract the x-axis as the column of interest
xs = threshed_q1_df[[COLUMN_OF_INTEREST_Q1]]

# Extract the y-values for distance and noise types
distance_ys = threshed_q1_df[relevant_distance_keys]
noise_ys = threshed_q1_df[relevant_noise_keys]

# Create the figure with the appropriate scale factor
fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(3.50*FIG_SCL,2.695*FIG_SCL), sharex=True)

# Axes style function
def style_axes(the_ax: plt.Axes, y_max: int, title: str) -> None:
    the_ax.set_xlim([0, PX_THRESHOLD])
    the_ax.set_ylim([0, y_max])
    the_ax.set_title(title, pad=2)

top = "g"
pri = "#000"
alt = "#777"
ax[0].set_prop_cycle(cycler('color', [top, pri, pri]) +
                     cycler('linestyle', ["-", "--", ":"]))
ax[1].set_prop_cycle(cycler('color', [top, alt, pri, alt, pri, pri]) +
                     cycler('linestyle', ["-", "--", "--", "-.", "-.", ":"]))

# Plot the distances on the top axes (scale ys by 100 for convinience)
ax[0].plot(xs, distance_ys*100, lw=1, label=["Near", "Medium", "Far"])
ax[0].legend(loc='upper right', ncol=3, bbox_to_anchor=(1, .9), prop={'size': "xx-small"})
style_axes(ax[0], 100, "Distance types")

# Plot the noises on the bottom axes (scale ys by 100 for convenience)
ax[1].plot(xs, noise_ys*100, lw=1, label=["No Noise", "Horizontal", "Vertical", "Grid", "Rotated Grid", "Salt"])
ax[1].legend(loc="lower right", ncol=2, bbox_to_anchor=(1.012, -0.035), prop={'size': "xx-small"})

# Create x and y label
fig.supylabel("Cumulative percentage of experiments", x=0.03);
fig.supxlabel("Mean reprojection error for surface geometry (px)", y=0.01)

# Save the figure to disk (Fig. 8)

Utility functions for 2D -> 3D estimation¶

In [ ]:
# Normalizes a given vector
def _normalize(v):
    norm = np.linalg.norm(v)
    if norm == 0:
        return v
    return v / norm

# Computes the intersection for a defined plane using a ray
def _line_plane_collision(plane_normal, plane_point, ray_direction, ray_point, epsilon=1e-6):
    ndotu = plane_normal.dot(ray_direction)
    if abs(ndotu) < epsilon:
        raise RuntimeError("no intersection or line is within plane")

    w = ray_point - plane_point
    si = -plane_normal.dot(w) / ndotu
    Psi = w + si * ray_direction + plane_point
    return Psi

# Estimates the world coordinate for a given pixel 
def _estimate_by_intersection(camera_matrix, t_vec, rotation_matrix, pixel_point, plane_point, plane_normal):
    inv_rotation_matrix = rotation_matrix.T # A transposed rotation matrix is its inverse
    inv_camera_matrix = np.linalg.inv(camera_matrix) # Inverse camera matrix (intrinsics)

    camera_rotation = inv_rotation_matrix  
    camera_position = (-(camera_rotation @ t_vec)).ravel()
    uv_point = np.array([pixel_point[0], pixel_point[1], 1])  # [u, v, 1]
    uv_point = inv_camera_matrix @ uv_point
    uv_point = camera_rotation @ uv_point

    ray_origin = camera_position  # .reshape(3,)#np.array([camera_translation[0], camera_translation[1], camera_translation[2]])
    ray_direction = uv_point  # np.array([uv_point[0], uv_point[1], uv_point[2]])
    ray_direction = _normalize(ray_direction)

    try:
        Psi = _line_plane_collision(plane_normal, plane_point, ray_direction, ray_origin)
    except RuntimeError as err:
        return [np.nan, np.nan, np.nan]

    return Psi.ravel()

# Define a camera dataclass for convenience
@dataclass
class Camera:
    camera_matrix: np.array
    t_vec: np.array
    r_vec: np.array
    rotation_matrix: np.array
    distortion: np.array

    @staticmethod
    def from_params(the_row) -> "Camera":
        fu, fv, cx, cy, tx, ty, tz, rx, ry, rz, d0, d1, d2, d3, d4 = the_row
        cm = np.array([fu, 0, cx, 0, fv, cy, 0, 0, 1]).reshape((3,3))
        t_vec, r_vec, dist_coeff = np.array([tx, ty, tz]), np.array([rx, ry, rz]), np.array([d0, d1, d2, d3, d4])
        rotation_matrix = np.zeros((3, 3))
        cv.Rodrigues(r_vec, rotation_matrix)
        return Camera(cm, t_vec, r_vec, rotation_matrix, dist_coeff)

def _gen_camera_columns_array(prefix: str):
    return [f"{prefix}{v}" for v in ["fu", "fv", "cx", "cy", "tx", "ty", "tz", "rx", "ry", "rz", "d0", "d1", "d2", "d3", "d4"]]

START_CAMERA_COLUMNS = _gen_camera_columns_array("s_")
TARGET_CAMERA_COLUMNS = _gen_camera_columns_array("t_")
RESULT_CAMERA_COLUMNS = _gen_camera_columns_array("r_")

def project_and_unproject(geometry, the_camera: Camera, real_camera: Camera, plane_point, plane_normal):
    t_vec = the_camera.t_vec
    r_vec = the_camera.r_vec
    r_mat = the_camera.rotation_matrix
    camera_matrix = the_camera.camera_matrix
    dist_coeff = the_camera.distortion

    real_t_vec = real_camera.t_vec
    real_r_vec = real_camera.r_vec
    real_r_mat = real_camera.rotation_matrix
    real_camera_matrix = real_camera.camera_matrix
    real_dist_coeff = real_camera.distortion

    # Geometry points on image obtained by "the_camera"
    projected_points = cv.projectPoints(geometry.world_points, r_vec, t_vec, camera_matrix, dist_coeff)[0].reshape((-1, 2))

    # Estimate image points by line-plane intersection in 3d space:
    unprojected_points = np.zeros((projected_points.shape[0], 3))
    for idx, point in enumerate(projected_points):
        unprojected_points[idx, :] = _estimate_by_intersection(real_camera_matrix, real_t_vec, real_r_mat, point, plane_point, plane_normal)

    return projected_points, unprojected_points



def draw_reprojection_map(the_ax, real_points, unprojected_points, x_label="Z-Location [m]", y_label="X-Location [m]", xticks = [0, 4.26]):
    real_y, real_x = real_points[:, 0], real_points[:, 2]
    computed_y, computed_x = unprojected_points[:, 0], unprojected_points[:, 2]
    u, v = computed_x - real_x, computed_y-real_y
#    u, v = real_x - computed_x, real_y - computed_y
    colors = sns.color_palette("Set1")
    the_ax.quiver(real_x, real_y, u, v, scale=1, scale_units="xy", angles="xy", width=0.0025)
    the_ax.plot([0.00, 4.26], [0.00, 0.00], color=colors[0], lw=0.5, ls="-")
    the_ax.plot([2.61, 4.26], [1.60, 1.60], color=colors[0], lw=0.5, ls="-")
    the_ax.plot([2.61, 4.26], [-1.60, -1.60], color=colors[0], lw=0.5, ls="-")
    the_ax.plot([4.26, 4.26], [-3.20, 3.20], color=colors[0], lw=0.5, ls="-")
    the_ax.plot([2.61, 2.61], [-3.20, -1.60], color=colors[0], lw=0.5, ls="-")
    the_ax.plot([2.61, 2.61], [3.20, 1.60], color=colors[0], lw=0.5, ls="-")

    the_ax.set_yticks([-3.2, 0, 3.2])
    the_ax.set_xticks(xticks)
#    the_ax.set_xticklabels(the_ax.get_xticks(), rotation = -90)

    the_ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    the_ax.set_ylabel(y_label)
    the_ax.set_xlim([0, 9.75])
    the_ax.set_ylim([-3.2, 3.2])
    the_ax.invert_yaxis()

def draw_with_camera(image, geometry, camera, color, thickness):
    A, t, r, d = camera.camera_matrix, camera.t_vec, camera.r_vec, camera.distortion
    render_geometry_with_camera(image, fitting_geometry, A, t, r, d, color, thickness)

def plot_surface_mapping(row_of_interest, FIG_SCL=1):
    start_camera = Camera.from_params(row_of_interest[START_CAMERA_COLUMNS]) # Extract the start camera
    target_camera = Camera.from_params(row_of_interest[TARGET_CAMERA_COLUMNS]) # Extract the target camera
    result_camera = Camera.from_params(row_of_interest[RESULT_CAMERA_COLUMNS]) # Extract the result camera

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(3.50*FIG_SCL, 2.695*FIG_SCL))
    gs = fig.add_gridspec(2, 2, wspace=0.025, hspace=0.05)

    ax0 = fig.add_subplot(gs[0, 0])
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(gs[0, 1])
    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(gs[1, 0])
    ax3 = fig.add_subplot(gs[1, 1])
    plt.setp(ax3.get_yticklabels(), visible=False)

    result_projected, result_unprojected = project_and_unproject(drawing_geometry, result_camera, target_camera, ground_point, ground_normal);
    start_projected, start_unprojected = project_and_unproject(drawing_geometry, start_camera, target_camera, ground_point, ground_normal);
    target_projected, target_unprojected = project_and_unproject(drawing_geometry, target_camera, target_camera, ground_point, ground_normal);


    image_shape = (600, 800, 3)

    start_image = np.zeros(image_shape, dtype=np.uint8)
    result_image = np.zeros(image_shape, dtype=np.uint8)

    draw_with_camera(start_image, fitting_geometry, target_camera, TARGET_COLOR, 2)
    draw_with_camera(result_image, fitting_geometry, target_camera, TARGET_COLOR, 2)


    for (x, y) in target_projected:
        pt = (int(x), int(y))
        cv.drawMarker(start_image, pt, TARGET_COLOR, cv.MARKER_CROSS, 16, 1)
        cv.drawMarker(result_image, pt, TARGET_COLOR, cv.MARKER_CROSS, 16, 1)

    draw_with_camera(start_image, fitting_geometry, start_camera, START_COLOR, 2)
    for (x, y) in start_projected:
        pt = (int(x), int(y))
        cv.drawMarker(start_image, pt, START_COLOR, cv.MARKER_CROSS, 16, 1)

    draw_with_camera(result_image, fitting_geometry, result_camera, RESULT_COLOR, 2)
    for (x, y) in result_projected:
        pt = (int(x), int(y))
        cv.drawMarker(result_image, pt, RESULT_COLOR, cv.MARKER_CROSS, 16, 1)


    ax0.imshow(start_image, interpolation="none")
    ax1.imshow(result_image, interpolation="none")
    ax0.set_axis_off()
    ax1.set_axis_off()


    draw_reprojection_map(ax2, drawing_geometry.world_points, start_unprojected, x_label="", y_label="")
    draw_reprojection_map(ax3, drawing_geometry.world_points, result_unprojected, x_label="", y_label="", xticks=[0, 4.26, 9.75])

    def hide_axis_ticks(axes):
        axes.tick_params(
            axis='both',
            which='both',
            bottom=False,
            top=False,
            left=False,
            right=False,
            labelbottom=True) # labels along the bottom edge are off

    hide_axis_ticks(ax2)
    hide_axis_ticks(ax3)

    ax0.set_title("Start projection", pad=2)
    ax1.set_title("Result projection", pad=2)

    fig.supxlabel("Z-Location [m]", y=0.01)
    ax2.set_ylabel("X-Location [m]", labelpad=-4)

    return fig
